article.headline: USC 68, Arizona State 65
article.story:
TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Eshaya Murphy had nine of her 11 points
during a decisive second-half run, and Southern California snapped
Arizona State's nine-game home winning streak with a 68-65 victory
over the Sun Devils on Saturday.

Reserve Rometra Craig also had 11 points for the Women of Troy
(8-7, 5-2 Pac-10). Jamie Hagiya and Meghan Gnekow scored 10 apiece,
and Ebony Hoffman contributed nine points, ten rebounds and three
steals.

Betsy Boardman led the Sun Devils (10-6, 4-3) with 15 points,
and Carrie Buckner had 12 points and five assists.

The Women of Troy had a 9-0 run early in the second half to take
a 39-35 lead with 14:34 to play.

Arizona State fought back to a 40-39 lead three minutes later,
but Gnekow started a 17-4 run with a jumper with 11:12 to go, and
Murphy made three jumpers, a layup and a free throw to spark USC to
a 56-44 lead with 5:44 to play.

The Sun Devils got close on 3-pointers by Boardman and YoVanna
Rosenthal in the final 26 seconds, but squandered a chance at
overtime when Kristen Kovesdy's 3-point attempt bounced off the rim
at the buzzer.

Arizona State led 20-11 with 6:07 left in the first half, but
USC closed took advantage of three Sun Devils turnovers to get
within 28-27 at halftime.
